        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(nodes): surface pending reapproval diagnostics",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add explicit node approval diagnostics to `node.list` and `node.describe`: `approved`, `pending-approval`, `pending-reapproval`, or `unapproved`, plus the pending request ID and explicitly named pending declared surfaces.\n- Merge the already-loaded `nodePairing.pending` snapshot into the known-node catalog without another store read.\n- Keep `caps`, `commands`, and `permissions` effective-only while `nodes status` / `nodes describe` explain approval vs reapproval and recommend `openclaw nodes approve <requestId>`.\n- Constrain privileged diagnostics to the configured local backend path, including supported loopback `auth.mode: \"none\"` gateways, while preserving read-only fallback for remote or unavailable privileged auth.\n- Clear stale reapproval only after a successful hello from the node connection that is still current; rejected, failed, refreshed, replaced, and overlapping reconnects preserve valid pending approval.\n- Do not change approval policy, auto-approve requests, or make pending declarations executable.\n\nRefs #84644\n\n## Verification\n\n- `PATH=/Users/jason/.nvm/versions/node/v24.14.0/bin:$PATH node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/program.nodes-basic.e2e.test.ts src/gateway/call.test.ts src/gateway/node-catalog.test.ts src/gateway/node-connect-reconcile.test.ts src/gateway/server.node-pairing-authz.test.ts src/gateway/server.node-version-mismatch.test.ts src/infra/node-pairing.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`\n  - Final result on `ec164667d6`: 18 files passed, 571 tests passed.\n  - Covers first approval vs reapproval, effective-vs-pending surfaces, list/describe diagnostics, scoped privileged fallback, local auth-none diagnostics, stale request IDs, terminal sanitization, successful stale cleanup, rejected/failed reconnect preservation, revision races, and overlapping reconnect ownership.\n- `pnpm format:check -- <17 touched TypeScript files>`\n  - Passed.\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs <17 touched TypeScript files>`\n  - Passed.\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n  - Passed.\n- `git diff --check`\n  - Passed.\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n  - Passed on Azure through Crabbox against final head `ec164667d6`.\n  - Run: https://crabbox.openclaw.ai/portal/runs/run_dae272da3fd5\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base upstream/main --codex-bin /Users/jason/.codex/openclaw-pr-autopilot/bin/codex-persist-sessions --model codex=kepler-alpha --thinking codex=high --stream-engine-output`\n  - Clean: no accepted/actionable findings; overall patch correct.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: A connected node can have a pending declared-surface reapproval while its effective command surface remains restricted; operators need the pending request ID, explicit reapproval state, and exact approval command.\n- Existing live environment attempt: An isolated foreground Gateway and real headless node-host CLI processes on macOS reached a connected loopback node. Loopback auto-approval prevented the requested manual initial-approval sequence; a LAN-bound retry reached the expected device-pairing trust boundary but lacked a pre-approved admin operator to complete the sequence.\n- Final maintenance proof: Real gateway websocket/client integration and CLI E2E tests exercise the current code path, including pending reapproval diagnostics, restricted effective commands, local auth-none access, successful stale cleanup, failed hello/version mismatch preservation, and overlapping reconnect ownership.\n- Observed result after fix: Pending declarations remain non-effective; pending diagnostics remain visible to an authorized local backend caller; valid pending approval survives rejected, failed, refreshed, replaced, and overlapping reconnects; a successful current reverted reconnect clears stale pending approval.\n- What was not tested: A complete real cross-host flow with an already-approved admin operator that approves the initial node surface, expands it, reconnects, and observes status/describe before reapproval.\n- Proof limitation: The patch intentionally does not add or use auto-approval to bypass the trust boundary needed for that cross-host scenario.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- Did user-visible behavior change? Yes, node status/describe now expose additive approval diagnostics and remediation.\n- Did config, environment, or migration behavior change? No.\n- Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? No approval or execution policy changed. Privileged diagnostics remain limited to the configured local backend path; remote and URL-override paths retain read-only fallback.\n- Highest-risk areas: Accidentally treating pending declarations as effective, over-broad privileged diagnostics auth, or deleting a valid pending request during reconnect races.\n- Mitigation: Focused negative-control and lifecycle tests cover effective-vs-pending surfaces, constrained auth, failed handshakes, revision changes, replacement requests, and overlapping current connections.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- Ready for maintainer review.\n- Final focused proof, final-head remote `check:changed`, and persisted `kepler-alpha/high` autoreview are clean.\n- ClawSweeper re-review requested after the maintenance push because its prior Codex review failed before producing a verdict.",
